## FAQs\
\
# Frequently Asked Questions\
\
You got questions? We got answers. You got other questions that aren't here? Ask us in one of our [support](./support-contribute.md) channels!\
\
## General\
\
<details>\
  <summary>Why should I use Coefficient?</summary>\
\
  The goal of Coefficient is to help teams at ORNL build faster, stay consistent, and deliver more accessible, higher-quality products. Lab leadership has repeatedly stressed the importance of UX and design in our application portfolio, and Coefficient is your force multiplier to help you get there without repaving all those roads yourself.\
</details>\
\
<details>\
  <summary>When should I start using Coefficient in my project?</summary>\
\
  The short answer is *as early as possible*. For some projects, such as anything built in Vuetify, we have plug-and-play tools to fit right into what you're already doing, If you're using Sharepoint or SAP you may be able to take advantage of our built-in themes. And in all cases, you can use one of our [UI Kits](./resources) to design your application.\
  \
  Unsure of where to begin? Check out our [Getting Started](./get-started/) guides. Or drop in on our Office Hours and various [support channels](./support-contribute) to ask us questions directly.\
</details>\
\
<details>\
  <summary>Why isn't my specific usage/design need already in the system?</summary>\
\
  We're constantly iterating on Coefficient and adapting to the needs and use cases we see emerging in the lab across many teams, applications, and divisions, so it's possible we just haven't gotten to it yet.\
\
However, it's important to note that a design system isn't meant to cover every possible design or implementation case in a plug-and-play way. The goal of Coefficient is to make "doing the right thing easy" and cover the common, broadly-applicable usage so that your team can focus on the application and domain-specific details.\
\
There's a balance to be struck with any prescriptive guidance/code between being useful enough to accellerate development and being too restrictive and becoming a burden, and we will always err on the side of not getting in your way.\
\
That said, if you feel like we're missing something important or want to talk more about how to adapt Coefficient to your specific needs, [reach out](./support-contribute)!\
</details>\
\
<details>\
  <summary>How do I report a bug or request a feature?</summary>\
\
  Reach out to the team for help by visiting [our support channels](./support-contribute) or come to our Office Hours.\
</details>\
\
## Design\
\
<details>\
  <summary>Can I customize or detach components?</summary>\
\
  Yes! While we recommend that you try to use the components out of the box as much as possible, you can detach and customize components as needed. Please use our tokens for any customizations and keep in mind accessibility requirements. \
</details>\
\
<details>\
  <summary>Where do I find common assets like logos and other images?</summary>\
  \
  We maintain an up to date list of approved reserouces on our [Brand](./fundamentals/brand) page.\
</details>\
\
## Develop\
\
<details>\
  <summary>What frameworks does Coefficient support?</summary>\
  \
  We aim to support most of the major frameworks and COTS platforms in use by the lab in some way. Check out our [framework support](./framework-support/) page for more details.\
</details>\
\
<details>\
  <summary>Can I used Coefficient with other design systems or component libraries?</summary>\
  \
  Yes! Our philosophy is to "meet teams where they are" and augment how you're already working rather than dictate new ways to work. We are investing a lot of time into finding ways to weave Coefficient into other commonly-used libraries, such as <Link to="/docs/coefficient/framework-support/vuetify">Vuetify</Link>, either by direct integration when there is a good mechanism for that to happen, or by giving you our <Link to="/docs/coefficient/framework-support/general-html-css-js">design tokens and compiled styles</Link> to plug into any HTML-based project.\
\
While we can't cover every possible framework out there, we are always looking for what integrations will make a big impact on how applications are developed at ORNL, so if there's support for a specific system or library that you want to talk about, [reach out](./support-contribute)! Or take a stab at building out those connectors yourself and [contributing back](./support-contribute) to Coefficient!\
</details>\
\
<details>\
  <summary>Where can I find the source code?</summary>\
  \
  All of our code is hosted on our internal Gitlab instance at [https://code.ornl.gov/ords/ornl-design-system](https://code.ornl.gov/ords/ornl-design-system). Anyone with internal access should be able to browse the repository or make a merge request.\
</details>\
\
<details>\
  <summary>How are code assets versioned?</summary>\
  \
  We practice [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/) for all code releases and in general will work to avoid breaking changes whenever possible. Because we're a small team, we don't have the resources or bandwidth to maintain and enhance multiple versions of software so in general, once released, a given previous version will not receive updates and patches on a parallel release branch from the current major version.\
</details>\
\
## Accessibility\
\
<details>\
  <summary>What accessibility standards has Coefficient implemented?</summary>\
  \
  Coefficient follows the [Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 AA](https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/) and [Section 508](https://www.section508.gov/) standards, so teams can create applications and websites that work for everyone. These standards guide our components, patterns, and documentation, and we\'e2\'80\'99ll keep updating them as new guidelines are released and followed. \
</details>\
\
<details>\
  <summary>What tools can I use to ensure accessibility in my application?</summary>\
  \
  There are many automated/semi-automated tools such as linters and accessibility testers available for almost any type of project you are working on. For an in-depth look at tools, check out our [Tools & Resources](./resources) page.\
</details>\
\
<details>\
  <summary>Why is accessibility a primary focus of Coefficient?</summary>\
  \
The short answer is: it's [a regulatory requirement](https://www.section508.gov/). The better answer is: everyone who uses applications and websites developed at the lab should be able to do so in a way that works well for them and allows them to be productive and happy (or at least not frustrated). "Everyone" is a big category with a lot of variables, and approaching UX in an accessibility-first way ensures that we're including as many people in that "everyone" as possible.\
</details>\
\
