## Our Philosophy\
\
ORNL builds across multiple technical frameworks (e.g. Vuetify, SAP Fiori, SharePoint, WordPress, Material UI, etc.) rather than a single unified tech stack. Traditional design systems that provide single component libraries don't work in this type of environment as they add friction when designers create framework-agnostic designs that require significant developer effort to implement.\
\
Coefficient solves this by providing framework-focused guidance and tools along with framework agnostic patterns, enabling efficient collaboration without forcing teams into one technical solution.\
\
### Comprehensive Patterns & Tools\
\
- Framework-agnostic guidance on UX patterns such as forms, headers, navigation flows\
- Platform-specific implementation best practices and tooling\
- Accessibility guidance embedded throughout\
- Shared foundations across all frameworks: colors, typography, iconography\
\
### Focused UI Kits by Framework\
\
- Figma UI kits tailored to each supported framework at the lab\
- Consistent \'e2\'80\'9csource of truth\'e2\'80\uc0\u157  foundational tokens across all UI kits\
- Platform-specific elements that matching actual developer tools\
\
:::note\
\
- Coefficient is not a single component library; unlike traditional design systems we don't force a single technical solution. We enable teams at ORNL to work with the grain of the frameworks they are already comfortable with.\
- Coefficient is not focused on coded components. Our primary focus is on enabling efficient designer-developer collaboration through tooling and guidance patterns (which *can* include coded components when needed)\
\
:::\
