### Markup\
\
- Using the correct tags for buttons is important because it can disorient users if they hear the wrong tag read out to them by the screen reader.\
- HTML\'c2\'a0`<button>`\'c2\'a0or\'c2\'a0`<input type="button">`:\'c2\'a0Buttons should be created created using the\'c2\'a0`<button>`\'c2\'a0or\'c2\'a0`<input>`\'c2\'a0tag with a\'c2\'a0type="button"\'c2\'a0attribute.\
\
## Accessibility\
\
### Human Impact Overview\
\
- Buttons facilitate user interaction by providing clear, clickable actions on web pages and applications.\
- For users with disabilities, buttons must be easy to identify and use, with alternative methods for interaction, such as keyboard controls.\
- Proper button design helps reduce confusion and ensures that all users can navigate more efficiently.\
\
### WCAG 2.1 A and AA Success Criteria\
\
- [1.4.1](https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/#use-of-color) Use of Color: Buttons should not rely solely on color to convey their function. Text labels or universally recognized icons could accompany them.\
- [2.4.7](https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/#focus-visible) Focus Visible: Buttons must have a visible focus indicator when navigated to via keyboard.\
- [4.1.2](https://www.w3.org/TR/UNDERSTANDING-WCAG20/ensure-compat-rsv.html) Name, Role, Value: Buttons must have clear names and roles defined to be operable and understandable by user agents, including assistive technologies.\
\
### Keep in mind\
\
- Buttons should display a visible focus state when users tab to them.\
- Screen readers handle buttons and links differently. Pressing the Space/Enter key triggers a button, but pressing the Enter key triggers a link.\
- Provide clear, concise labels for all actions to support users with cognitive disabilities.\
  Avoid using generic labels like \'e2\'80\'9cClick Here\'e2\'80\uc0\u157  for buttons. Use more informative and descriptive labels. Please see our [Guidance](#label) for recommendations.\
\
### Keyboard Interaction\
\
- All buttons must be accessible using the keyboard alone.\
- Buttons can be reached by tab\'c2\'a0and selected with\'c2\'a0space\'c2\'a0or\'c2\'a0enter.\
\
