Teams using Vuetify can directly leverage its [v-app-bar](https://vuetifyjs.com/en/components/app-bars) or [v-toolbar](https://vuetifyjs.com/en/components/toolbars) components. The slot architecture maps well to Vuetify's layout logic by utilizing the v-spacer component to control alignment.\
\
- **Branding Slot:** Use the `v-app-bar-title` or `v-toolbar-title` component (depending on which root component you selected). This ensures the logo or site title remains anchored to the left.\
- **Navigation Slot:** Place top-level navigation items immediately after the branding title. Note: For mobile layouts, use v-app-bar-nav-icon to house collapsed navigation which will help implement the [Responsive Behavior](#responsive-behavior) guidance from above.\
- **The Split (Spacer):** Insert a `<v-spacer></v-spacer>` component after the navigation items. This can be used to push everything following it to the align to the right, creating the separation between Navigation and User Actions.\
- **User Actions Slot:** Place icon buttons or toggles after the spacer to anchor them to the right.\
