## Typography\
\
Guidance and accessibility best practices to help enhance the readability of typography in our user experiences.\
\
## How we think about typography\
\
### Typography establishes hierarchy\
\
Hierarchy is how we visually communicate order. A structured heirarchy will help our users answer:\
\
- Where should my attention go first?\
- How is this content organized?\
- What belongs together?\
\
Size, weight, spacing, and positioning work together to establish visual prominence and guide users through content at a glance. Consistent hierarchy supports scannability, especially in data-dense environments or long-form sections.\
\
Hierarchy is about clarity. It\'e2\'80\'99s the structure that makes information instantly understandable.\
\
### Typography defines purpose\
\
Purpose helps define when a given style should be used and what you want the user to recognize.\
\
When selecting type which type token to use for a given purpose, consider these questions:\
\
- Is this text introducing, informing, or inviting action?\
- Is this content primary or supporting?\
\
Purpose ensures that each type style is used intentionally rather than decoratively. It allows us to make consistent decisions:\
\
- Display call for attention\
- Heading groups and structures content\
- Body supports comfortable reading\
- Link communicate interactivity\
\
Purpose is about intention. It\'e2\'80\'99s how we choose the right tool for the job.\
\
