\
### Body\
\
Best for comfortable, long-form reading, dense content areas, lists and paragraphs.\
\
#### Body properties\
\
- Regular weight (400) for legibility\
- Line-height of 1.5 to reduce eye fatigue\
- Subtle letter spacing (+0.02em) for clarity at smaller sizes\
\
#### Body sizes\
\
- XL (1.5rem) \'e2\'80\'93 prominent text blocks, feature copy\
- Large and Medium (1.25rem / 1rem) \'e2\'80\'93 standard paragraph text\
- Small, XS, XXS (0.875rem / 0.75rem / 0.625rem) \'e2\'80\'93 captions, supporting text\
\
#### Body is good for\
\
- Article-style content\
- List views and tables\
- UI supporting text and captions\
\
### Link\
\
Link can be used to communicate interactive, actionable text\
\
#### Link properties\
\
- Matches body weights, line-heights and sizes\
- Always include underline styling out-of-the-box\
\
## Guidance\
\
### Text spacing\
\
Our tokens meet recommended accessibility standards for line height, letter spacing, and word spacing ratios to ensure readability.  If you are not able to leverage our tokens directly please implement the specs listed for each font style to meet the same standards manually.\
\
**Why is this important?**\
Adequate spacing improves readability for all users, especially for those with dyslexia or cognitive disabilities.\
\
**Accessibility standard we follow**\
WCAG 2.1, 1.4.12 Text Spacing (Level AA) ([Reference](https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/Understanding/text-spacing.html))\
\
- Line height (line spacing) to at least 1.5 times the font size;\
- Spacing following paragraphs to at least 2 times the font size;\
- Letter spacing (tracking) to at least 0.12 times the font size;\
- Word spacing to at least 0.16 times the font size.\
\
### Text resizing\
\
Our components support zoom up to 200% without loss of content or functionality by default.\
\
**Why is this important?**\
Some users, especially those with low vision, rely on browser zoom to read content. Text that does not scale properly can become unreadable or cause layout issues.\
\
**Accessibility standard we follow**\
WCAG 2.1, 1.4.4 Resize Text (Level AA) ([Reference](https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/Understanding/resize-text.html))\
\
- Ensure text remains readable when users zoom up to 200% without loss of content or functionality.\
- Support responsive typography that adapts to different devices and user settings.\
- Avoid fixed pixel heights for containers that could cause text clipping.\
