Source: ["Readability: The Optimal Line Length"](https://baymard.com/blog/line-length-readability) by Baymard Institute \
\
The ideal line length is around 50-75 characters, including spaces, or 12-14 words per line. Longer lines of text can feel intimidating and overwhelming to users, potentially leading them to avoid reading. Conversely, lines that are too short disrupt the reader\'e2\'80\'99s rhythm by requiring frequent eye movements.\
